cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of partial and imperfect feedback on the performance of an OFDMA downlink system. Information theory is concerned with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information, which is relevant to this paper. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the design of a heterogeneous feedback system in an OFDMA downlink, which is a networking and internet architecture problem. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the impact of channel statistics on the design of a feedback system, which is relevant to social and information networks. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the downlink transmission of multimedia data in an OFDMA system, which falls under the scope of multimedia. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses an analytical framework to investigate the impact of partial and imperfect feedback, which is a computational engineering problem.
